member.summary:
Defines a Pade approximant.

More information can be found on the website:
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pad%C3%A9_approximant.

Example: exp(x) = 1 + x + x^2/2! + x^3/3! + ...

float[] taylorExp = new float[] { 1.0f, 1.0f, 0.5f, 1.0f/6.0f, 1.0f/24.0f, 1.0f/120.0f, 1.0f/720.0f };
var pade = new Pade(2, 2);
var (n, d) = pade.Compute(taylorExp);

            Creates a stereo effect for a pair of images UMapxing to the following calculations:


Ra=0.299*Rl+0.587*Gl+0.114*Bl;

Ga=0;

Ba=0.299*Rr+0.587*Gr+0.114*Br.

            Creates a stereo effect for a pair of images UMapxing to the following calculations:


Ra=0.299*Rl+0.587*Gl+0.114*Bl;

Ga=0.299*Rr+0.587*Gr+0.114*Br;

Ba=0.299*Rr+0.587*Gr+0.114*Br.

            Creates a stereo effect for a pair of images UMapxing to the following calculations:


Ra=Rl;

Ga=Gr;

Ba=Br.

            Creates a stereo effect for a pair of images UMapxing to the following calculations:


Ra=0.299*Rl+0.587*Gl+0.114*Bl;

Ga=Gr;

Ba=Br.

            Creates a stereo effect for a pair of images UMapxing to the following calculations:


Ra=0.7*Gl+0.3*Bl;

Ga=Gr;

Ba=Br.

